values: OMG! Can you BELIEVE it's actually SUMMER?  This is so awesome.  Yea, so if anyone wants to do anything, call pleassssse.

Okay, so I just finished this wickid awesome book.  Seriouly, it's like the best book ever.  It's called "Someone like you" and it's by Sarah Dessen.  It's 281 pages, and it always keeps you on the edge.  Sorry, I'm like doing a book review, but whatever it's so good.  Without giving anything more than what would be on the back of the book, here is a brief description:  It's about this girl named Halley (who tells the story) and she's had her best friend Scarlett since they were eleven years old.  Now they are sixteen, and Scarlett's boyfriend dies (don't worry, that doesn't give anything away).  Well Scarlett later finds out that the she is pregnant with his baby.  Meanwhile, Halley is busy with her own relationship, in which her parents disapprove of, and Halley and her mother are drifting further apart.  The story is about Halley and Scarlett's struggles, and how good friends come through for eachother.  It's probably the best book I've ever read.  You should really read it!!!
2 days left, and then OUT FOR SUMMER!!!!!!!!

Hey.  Tonight we're performing The Music Man.  That should be fun.  Jackie is Marian, and she has such a good voice.  I'm going to Aruba this Summer with my family and the Riccis.  That'll be so much fun!!!  Now my August is fully booked: week 1- camp, week 2- Aruba, week 3 and 4- volunteering at a camp for children with Autism.  15 more days of school!!!!!!!!!

HAPPY EASTER!!!
and Happy Birthday Abby!!!!!!!
I'm sleepin over Deana's tonight.  YAY!!!!
I'm goin to the movies with Dan today!!! Can't wait!!!!!
Ever get in trouble for something your sister did?  Now you know how I feel.

Last night Steph, Alyssa, and Abby came over.  We watched "Roll Bounce" which is a good movie, and played the cup game with water bottles.  It was really fun.  I LOVE the cup game. It's so much fun- and very addicting. After I play I always have the rythem stuck in my head, but i's REALLY fun!!!!!!
Tonight I'm sleeping over Melissa's.  I can't wait!!!

A few words to sum up the wake- 4 and a half hours, boring, SAD, lots of coloring with Megan because of boredom, lots of crying, lots of talking, lots of hugging, lots of family, lots of friends, lots of comforting, lots of being comforted, lots of "sorry"s, lots of "thank you"s

The Funeral:
Clammy hands I wiped on dress
Teary eyes I wiped on arm 
Prayed with all my heart
Cried with all my tears

Life is getting easier.  People aren't as sad all the time, which is nice.  I've been seeing Gram a lot lately, and she's doing well.  Life is pretty much back to normal.  People aren't crying.  The wake and funeral are over.  We don't have much to be nervous about anymore.  I miss my Pennsylvania relitives, but hopefully we'll see them soon enough.  I was afraid New Years Eve mass would be sad, but surprisingly it wasn't.  We will always remember Papa's smiling face, and we'll always miss him too. Now, we can celebrate his wonderful life, and cherish our memories of him.
OMG!  I can't believe we had a snow day today!  There was hardly any snow!!  Well, wutever- it works 4 me!!!
I miss Papa asking me if I can spell my name yet.

I miss Papa calling me honey-bunch
I miss Papa saying he loves me
I miss Papa's big hugs
I miss Papa telling me to kiss him on the cheek
I miss Papa telling me "That's not a kiss!"
I miss Papa kissing me on the cheek
I miss Papa's buzz cut right after his hair cut
I miss Papa calling me Henrietta when he forgets my name
I miss Papa's smile
I miss Papa's laugh
I miss Papa's words of wisdom
I miss the little bit of sweet potato under Papa's chin
I MISS PAPA!!!

I Love You, Papa.
You will always remain in our hearts!
  12/14/1916 -12/25/2005

I just saw "Cheaper by the Dozen 2" with Alex, Devin, and Abby.  It was really good!!!!!!  The ending wuz awesome!  3 days till Christmas!!!  Can u believe the day after tomorrow iz Christmas Eve?  OMG, it's come so quick!!!  Happy Holidays everyone!

2day was kinda boring, cuz no1 else is out of skool yet, so there was
nobody 2 call or IM. I finished the second clique book, "Best Friends
for Never", as well as a rather depressing book called "Stop
Pretending". I recomend the the clique books, and I'm glad my friends
told me about them. As for "Stop Pretending", it's pretty sad, but it's
a quick read, so it's not that bad. "A Christmas Carol" was very good
this year. I love Trinity! We had to read the book in English class,
which was pretty long, and hard to read, considering the time given. I
think one year, Trinity should do the play just like Dickens' book,
like word for word, scene for scene. Wouldn't that be cool. I am
beginning to lose hope in Livejournal. Now everyone is hooked on
myspace, and has either abandoned their livejournal or deleted it. I
still like livejournal, and that's why I'm so disapointed. If you read
this, can you please just put a coment on this entry, so I know who
read it; because I don't think many ppl do anymore. 6 days till
Christmas!!!

Why is it that when I finally have just one subject of homework, which is to study for a test, I can only be on the computer for 15 minutes,and then Brenna can go on the computer?  Normally, I never go on the computer on school days because I'm doing homework all night.  Now I still can't go on.  UGH!!  Also, why is it that my dad won't let me have a myspace, but it's just fine for Brenna to have one?
